Manchester United manager, Ole Gunnar Solskjaer, has branded Scott McTominay “undroppable”, after his performance in the 2-1 win over Tottenham on Wednesday. McTominay missed three games through injury, but made himself available to face Spurs after completing just one training session. “You can almost say he is undroppable at the moment. “The physical presence he gives us, the leadership he gives us in midfield, he also releases Fred. “He trained yesterday [Tuesday] and that was just a light session with the reserves but he’s a tough boy. “There was no chance he was going to say ‘no thanks’ if he felt OK. “It’s probably the first time I’ve really really pushed players that haven’t had the foundation but he’s so fit anyway,” Solskjaer told Amazon. Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.